# =============================================================================
# Supabase Configuration
# =============================================================================
#
# To set up your own Supabase backend:
#
# 1. Create a free account at https://supabase.com
# 2. Click "New Project" and give it a name (e.g. "co-captain")
# 3. Wait for the project to finish provisioning
# 4. Go to Project Settings → API (https://supabase.com/dashboard/project/_/settings/api)
# 5. Copy the following values:
#
#    - "Project ID"   → shown in the URL: https://supabase.com/dashboard/project/<PROJECT_ID>
#    - "Project URL"  → listed under "Project URL" (e.g. https://<PROJECT_ID>.supabase.co)
#    - "anon public"  → listed under "Project API keys" (the publishable/anon key, NOT the secret key)
#
# 6. Paste them below and restart the dev server (npm run dev)
#
# Note: The anon key is safe to commit — it only works with Row Level Security (RLS)
# policies and does not grant admin access to your database.
# =============================================================================

